GOLDMINE PRIVACY POLICY
Effective Date: April 9, 2023
Introduction
Goldmine is a mobile game developed using Unity engine and is published by [Insert your company name]. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and share information about you when you play Goldmine.
Unity Engine
Goldmine is developed using the Unity engine. As a result, Unity may collect certain data from your device when you use the game. This data may include your device type, operating system, IP address, and other technical information. Unity uses this data to provide and improve their services, as well as to personalize your experience with Goldmine. For more information about how Unity collects and uses data, please see their privacy policy:
https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
.
Unity Ads
We use Unity Ads to display in-game ads to you. Unity Ads may collect certain information about your device and how you interact with the ads, such as your IP address, device type, and ad engagement data. Unity Ads uses this information to provide and improve their ad services, as well as to personalize the ads you see. For more information about how Unity Ads collects and uses data, please see their privacy policy:
https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy#advertising_data
.
Unity Analytics
We use Unity Analytics to track certain information about your gameplay, such as your in-game progress and achievements. Unity Analytics may also collect certain technical information about your device, such as your device type and operating system. Unity Analytics uses this information to provide and improve their analytics services, as well as to personalize your gameplay experience. For more information about how Unity Analytics collects and uses data, please see their privacy policy:
https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy#analytics_data
.
How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect from you to provide and improve Goldmine. Specifically, we use your information to:
Deliver and personalize your gameplay experience.
Display relevant in-game ads.
Analyze how you use Goldmine to improve the game.
Communicate with you regarding updates or issues with Goldmine.
We do not sell your information to third parties.
How We Share Your Information
We may share your information with third-party service providers who help us provide and improve Goldmine, such as Unity Ads and Unity Analytics. We may also share your information as required by law or to protect our legal rights.
Your Choices
You have certain choices regarding the information we collect from you:
You can opt-out of certain data collection by adjusting your device settings or by uninstalling Goldmine.
You can also opt-out of personalized ads by visiting the Digital Advertising Alliance’s opt-out page:
https://optout.aboutads.info/
.
If you do not want us to use your information for analytics purposes, you can disable analytics in Goldmine's settings.
Please note that opting-out of certain data collection may impact your ability to use Goldmine.
Children’s Privacy
Goldmine is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe that we may have collected personal information from a child under 13, please contact us immediately.
Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no data transmission over the internet or electronic storage system can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Please take care in sharing your personal information with us.
Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make any material changes, we will notify you by posting a prominent notice on our website or
Page updated
Google Sites
Report abuse
This site uses cookies from Google to deliver its services and to analyze traffic. Information about your use of this site is shared with Google. By using this site, you agree to its use of cookies.
